reviewText: bad acting and hard to hear exactly what is being said. Actually looks and sounds as if it was shot on a cell phone. Gave up watching after 10 minutes.

Wil did a great job! Superb performance...edgy and compelling!!

This was definitely one of the most epic martial arts movies I have seen in a long time! Not only is the fight choreography fantastic, but there is true character development in several of the characters, and the plot is incredibly intriguing! Just when you think you know when how the movie is going to end, you find out that you're dead wrong!

Genuinely engaging story line, excellent and skillful martial arts/taekwondo/fight scenes. Very well acted and well written. Would write more but don't want to go into spoiler alert. A really great indie flick. Definitely recommend!
